gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pacers 126, Bucks 124
gameRecap.excerpt: Tyrese Haliburton led the Pacers with 29 points, 10 assists, and six rebounds as Indiana defeated Milwaukee, 126-124. Bennedict Mathurin (26 points, 11 rebounds) and Myles Turner (21 points, six rebounds, four assists) totaled 47 points as Indiana shot 21-49 from beyond the arc. Giannis Antetotokounmpo led the Bucks with 54 points (19-25), 12 rebounds, and three assists in the losing effort. The Pacers improve to 6-3 as the Bucks move to 5-3 on the season.
